urls.title: The musician-artist and author-scientist discuss how to live in right relationship to the land
urls.description: For our October episode, musician-artist Björk talks with author-scientist Robin Wall Kimmerer across subjects ranging from how language connects us to the natural world; the consequences—both personal and global—of living apart from nature; and what it means in our transient society to live in right relationship to the land. Bjork’s latest album, Fossora, is out with One Little Independent Records. Robin Wall Kimmerer’s most recent book, Braiding Sweetgrass: Indigenous Wisdom, Scientific Knowledge and the Teachings of Plants, is available from Milkweed Editions. [Note: this episode is available in audio format only.] Björk: Hello Robin! Robin Wall Kimmerer: Hello! Nice to meet you. Björk: Oh I just have to say, I have been enjoying your books so much.
